   "source": [
    ".. index:: Equations; Cahn-Hilliard\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cahn-Hilliard\n",
    "In this script we show how to use the $C^1$ non-conforming virtual\n",
    "element space to solve the Cahn-Hilliard equation. We use a fully implicit\n",
    "scheme here. You can find more details in <cite data-cite=\"VEM\"></cite>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "5ac8173a",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-12-02T17:54:08.993169Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-12-02T17:54:08.992903Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-12-02T17:54:10.332437Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-12-02T17:54:10.331469Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    import dune.vem\n",
    "except:\n",
    "    print(\"This example needs 'dune.vem' - skipping\")\n",
    "    import sys\n",
    "    sys.exit(0)\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot\n",
    "import random\n",
    "from dune.grid import cartesianDomain, gridFunction\n",
    "import dune.fem\n",
    "from dune.fem.plotting import plotPointData as plot\n",
    "from dune.fem.function import discreteFunction\n",
    "\n",
    "from ufl import *\n",
    "import dune.ufl\n",
    "\n",
    "dune.fem.threading.use = 4"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5e1e9124",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    "Grid and space construction - we use a cube grid here:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "814a1d53",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-12-02T17:54:10.334987Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-12-02T17:54:10.334703Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.813808Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.812853Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "order        = 3\n",
    "polyGrid = dune.vem.polyGrid( cartesianDomain([0,0],[1,1],[30,30]), cubes=True)\n",
    "testSpaces = [ [0], [order-3,order-2], [order-4] ]\n",
    "# testSpaces   = [ [0,0],[order-4,order-3], [order-4] ]\n",
    "space = dune.vem.vemSpace(polyGrid, order=order, testSpaces=testSpaces)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6fc9c9b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To define the mathematical model, let $\\psi\\colon{\\mathbb R} \\rightarrow\n",
    "\\mathbb{R}$ be defined as\n",
    "$\\psi(x) = \\frac{(1-x^2)^2}{4}$ and let $\\phi(x) = \\psi(x)^{\\prime}$.\n",
    "The strong form for the solution\n",
    "$u\\colon \\Omega \\times [0,T] \\rightarrow {\\mathbb R}$\n",
    "is given by\n",
    "\\begin{align*}\n",
    "\\partial_t u  - \\Delta (\\phi(u)-\\epsilon^2 \\Delta u) = 0\n",
    "\\quad &\\text{in} \\ \\Omega \\times [0,T] ,\\\\\n",
    "u(\\cdot,0) = u_0(\\cdot)  \\quad &\\text{in} \\ \\Omega,\\\\\n",
    "\\partial_n u = \\partial_n \\big( \\phi(u) - \\epsilon^2\\Delta u \\big) = 0\n",
    "\\quad &\\text{on} \\ \\partial \\Omega \\times [0,T].\n",
    "\\end{align*}\n",
    "\n",
    "We use a backward Euler discretization in time and will fix the constant\n",
    "further down:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "44fae142",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.815927Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.815738Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.826670Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.825838Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "t     = dune.ufl.Constant(0,\"time\")\n",
    "tau   = dune.ufl.Constant(0,\"dt\")\n",
    "eps   = dune.ufl.Constant(0,\"eps\")\n",
    "df_n  = discreteFunction(space, name=\"oldSolution\") # previous solution\n",
    "x     = SpatialCoordinate(space)\n",
    "u     = TrialFunction(space)\n",
    "v     = TestFunction(space)\n",
    "\n",
    "H     = lambda v: grad(grad(v))\n",
    "laplace = lambda v: H(v)[0,0]+H(v)[1,1]\n",
    "a     = lambda u,v: inner(H(u),H(v))\n",
    "b     = lambda u,v: inner( grad(u),grad(v) )\n",
    "W     = lambda v: 1/4*(v**2-1)**2\n",
    "dW    = lambda v: (v**2-1)*v\n",
    "\n",
    "equation = ( u*v + tau*eps*eps*a(u,v) + tau*b(dW(u),v) ) * dx == df_n*v * dx\n",
    "\n",
    "dbc = [dune.ufl.DirichletBC(space, 0, i+1) for i in range(4)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# energy\n",
    "Eint  = lambda v: eps*eps/2*inner(grad(v),grad(v))+W(v)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "59f14e4d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next we construct the scheme providing some suitable expressions to stabilize the method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "ca047904",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.828304Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.828130Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.924720Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.923702Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "biLaplaceCoeff = eps*eps*tau\n",
    "diffCoeff      = 2*tau\n",
    "massCoeff      = 1\n",
    "scheme = dune.vem.vemScheme(\n",
    "                       [equation, *dbc],\n",
    "                       solver=(\"suitesparse\",\"umfpack\"),\n",
    "                       hessStabilization=biLaplaceCoeff,\n",
    "                       gradStabilization=diffCoeff,\n",
    "                       massStabilization=massCoeff,\n",
    "                       boundary=\"derivative\") # only fix the normal derivative = 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4b9f8baa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To avoid problems with over- and undershoots we project the initial\n",
    "conditions into a linear lagrange space before interpolating into the VEM\n",
    "space:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0d00c6a8",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.926614Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-12-02T17:54:11.926393Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-12-02T17:54:12.051389Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-12-02T17:54:12.050620Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def initial(x):\n",
    "    h = 0.01\n",
    "    g0 = lambda x,x0,T: conditional(x-x0<-T/2,0,conditional(x-x0>T/2,0,sin(2*pi/T*(x-x0))**3))\n",
    "    G  = lambda x,y,x0,y0,T: g0(x,x0,T)*g0(y,y0,T)\n",
    "    return 0.5*G(x[0],x[1],0.5,0.5,50*h)\n",
    "initial = dune.fem.space.lagrange(polyGrid,order=1).interpolate(initial(x),name=\"initial\")\n",
    "df = space.interpolate(initial, name=\"solution\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f85f22b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally the time loop - for the final coarsening phase (time greater than 0.8)\n",
    "we increase the time step a bit:"

   "source": [
    "t.value = 0\n",
    "eps.value = 0.05\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = pyplot.figure(figsize=(30,30))\n",
    "count = 0\n",
    "pos = 1\n",
    "while t.value < 2.15:\n",
    "    if t.value < 0.6:\n",
    "        tau.value = 1e-02\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        tau.value = 5e-02\n",
    "    df_n.assign(df)\n",
    "    info = scheme.solve(target=df)\n",
    "    t.value += tau\n",
    "    count += 1\n",
    "    if count % 10 == 0:\n",
    "        df.plot(figure=(fig,330+pos),colorbar=None,clim=[-1,1])\n",
    "        energy = dune.fem.integrate(Eint(df),order=3)\n",
    "        print(\"[\",pos,\"]\",t.value,tau.value,energy,info,flush=True)\n",
    "        pos += 1"
   ]
  }
